Description: Matching the world’s best dogs with the world’s best people.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: They mission here at Peace and Paws is to match the world’s best dogs with the world’s best people. They are committed to improving the lives of these animals, supporting spay and neuter education and trap-neuter-and-return programs, and continually finding ways to preserve the well-being of these rescued animals. They are a non-profit, all volunteer, foster-based rescue committed to saving they treasured friends from high-kill shelters. Peace and Paws is a 501(c)3 nonprofit dog rescue that began as a result from they own adoption experience. They started Peace and Paws by going through the adoption process themselves (a lot like what you are doing now). They adopted a phenomenal dog from Alabama and wanted to make more of a difference for these incredible and deserving dogs. They have successfully adopted more than 2,000 dogs and counting. Through they rescue work with Peace and Paws, they saw a need for safe, reliable transportation for the dogs and founded Rescue Riders Transport in 2008. They have been transporting dogs to other rescue groups, foster homes and adopters twice a month ever since. Rescue Riders Transport is USDA certified and fully compliant with local and state laws. They have met so many wonderful people along the way. They adopters, volunteers, foster homes and donors are the backbone of Peace and Paws. The Peace and Paws family is a team of many with these common goals: to help as many homeless dogs as possible and give adopters a positive rescue experience. It has been an amazing, inspiring and rewarding journey that they would not trade for the world.

Description: Sal's Pizzeria Mission Viejo, CA Pizza Delivery, Catering and Pickup
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Welcome to Sal's Pizzeria. Our restaurant was founded by Sal's son-in-law, Matthew Darienzo, out of his love and respect for both Sal and the traditional pizza he makes. Sal's Pizzeria is excited to bring the best pizza in Mission Viejo, California to pizza lovers in Orange County. Our pizza is made with authentic NY style, and we're proud to offer Grandma Pie pizza and Sicilian pizza (thick crust). In addition to pizza, we also have garlic knots, sandwiches, salads, pastas, calzones, desserts and more. Our goal is to provide our customers with a great pizza experience, and we're committed to offering the best possible product and service. Thanks for choosing Sal's Pizzeria! Sal (born in Sicily, Italy) came to America as a young man and eventually settled in Brooklyn, New York. It was there that he met and married Matthew's mother-in-law. They started a family and Sal began working in pizzerias to support them. He quickly developed a reputation for making the best pizzas around. When Matthew expressed an interest in opening his own pizzeria, Sal taught him everything he knew. Now, we carry on Sal's legacy by serving up delicious Sicilian. Looking for the best pizza in Mission Viejo, CA? Look no further than Sal's Pizzeria! We offer authentic NY Pizza, and Grandma Pie pizza, Sicilian pizza (thick crust) and Italian food favorites like garlic knots, sandwiches, salads, pastas, calzones, desserts and more. Our pizzas are made with the freshest ingredients and our dough is made fresh daily. Come try our famous thin crust pizza or our new gluten free pizza today! We guarantee you'll be back for more!

Description: The premier place for eye care and eyewear in Dallas, Texas.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: The Hargrave Eye Center is an ophthalmic center in Dallas, Texas. It is located on the campus of Methodist Dallas Medical Center in Pavilion III. They are known for their outstanding customer service and loyalty to their patients.  The office is modern in style and always clean, warm and inviting. The Hargrave Eye Center houses the latest technology for diagnosis and treatment.  They work as a team, enabling the patients to understand their symptoms and conditions, all the treatment options, and have their questions  answered.   The Hargrave Eye Center performs full service eye care. They are able to treat patients in multiple areas of ophthalmology including cataract and refractive surgery, cornea and external disease, glaucoma, diabetes, and uveitis. Screening for contact lenses and glasses can also be performed. The Hargrave Eye Center is owned and operated by Sylvia Hargrave, MD FACS. Dr. Hargrave  is currently the Chief of Ophthalmology and Ophthalmic Trauma at Methodist Dallas Medical Center, one of the oldest and most well-respected hospitals in Dallas.   Dr. Hargrave was recruited by Paul Farrow, director of physician recruiting, and Howard Chase, former president of Methodist Medical Center in 2002.  Methodist Dallas Medical Center has been recognized among the Top Performers on Key Quality Measures™ by The Joint Commission for achieving excellence in using evidence-based clinical processes that are shown to improve patient care. Dr. Hargrave was honored to be recruited to head the ophthalmology department at Methodist Medical Center. Since 1927, Methodist Dallas Medical Center has served North Texas as a leader in sophisticated, compassionate medical care with world-class medical education and residency programs.  Methodist Dallas Medical Center is also the main referral center for Methodist Health System and one of the leading hospitals in Texas.  Methodist Dallas Medical Center hospital features all-private rooms with 515 beds and a medical staff of over 250 physicians with expertise in over 60 medical specialties. Established by Dr. Hargrave, The Hargrave Eye Center has become a go-to for all types of vision appointments—from routine checkups to emergency concerns. The success of the Hargrave Eye Center is a reflection of Dr. Hargrave’s extensive education,  distinct experience, and renown ties to the surrounding medical community.
